The paper deals with sampling and reconstruction of multidimensional signals, specifically in the context of video sequences. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of compressive sensing (cs.SP) and weighted $\ell_1$-minimization methods, which are common techniques in signal processing and information theory (cs.IT, cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of a weight matrix based on the human visuality system, which suggests a focus on machine learning and perception (cs.LG, cs.MM).
